Pre-Game Insights: Both sides playing first game - they are in Group B alongside England, Australia and Scotland
Both are appearing in their third T20 World Cup
JJ Smit has had a terrific couple of years, scoring his runs for Namibia at a strike-rate of 151 and a mammoth average of 66
Gerhard Erasmus has taken nearly 30 wickets at an average of 12 in this World Cup cycle and concedes fewer than a run-a-ball
Aqib Ilyas is Oman’s leading run-scorer in the past 18 months and is the newly appointed captain for the World Cup
Bilal Khan is Oman’s left-arm yorker specialist. He has taken 106 wickets for Oman in his T20 career
